KW  - Discrete choice
KW  - Stochastic utility maximization
KW  - Random utility models
AB  - Börsch-Supan (1990) gives a sufficient condition for the compatibility of choice probabilities with stochastic utility maximization on an interval. We show that the necessary and sufficient conditions for global compatibility as derived by Daly and Zachary (1979) and McFadden (1981) also apply if the nonrandom components are restricted to a closed interval. Hence, this case gives no further restrictions on the choice probabilities.
